verses.text_plain: Now these are the nations which the Lord left, to prove Israel by them, even as many of Israel as had not known all the wars of Canaan;
verses.verse_html: 1Now these are the nations which the Lord left, to prove Israel by them, even as many of Israel as had not known all the wars of Canaan;

verses.text_plain: Only that the generations of the children of Israel might know, to teach them war, at the least such as before knew nothing thereof;
verses.verse_html: 2Only that the generations of the children of Israel might know, to teach them war, at the least such as before knew nothing thereof;

tokens.text: at the least such as before

verses.text_plain: Namely, five lords of the Philistines, and all the Canaanites, and the Sidonians, and the Hivites that dwelt in mount Lebanon, from mount Baal–hermon unto the entering in of Hamath.
verses.verse_html: 3Namely, five lords of the Philistines, and all the Canaanites, and the Sidonians, and the Hivites that dwelt in mount Lebanon, from mount Baal–hermon unto the entering in of Hamath.

verses.text_plain: And they were to prove Israel by them, to know whether they would hearken unto the commandments of the Lord, which he commanded their fathers by the hand of Moses.
verses.verse_html: 4And they were to prove Israel by them, to know whether they would hearken unto the commandments of the Lord, which he commanded their fathers by the hand of Moses.

verses.text_plain: And the children of Israel dwelt among the Canaanites, Hittites, and Amorites, and Perizzites, and Hivites, and Jebusites:
verses.verse_html: 5And the children of Israel dwelt among the Canaanites, Hittites, and Amorites, and Perizzites, and Hivites, and Jebusites:

verses.text_plain: And they took their daughters to be their wives, and gave their daughters to their sons, and served their gods.
verses.verse_html: 6And they took their daughters to be their wives, and gave their daughters to their sons, and served their gods.

verses.text_plain: And the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the Lord, and forgat the Lord their God, and served Baalim and the groves.
verses.verse_html: 7And the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the Lord, and forgat the Lord their God, and served Baalim and the groves.

verses.text_plain: Therefore the anger of the Lord was hot against Israel, and he sold them into the hand of Chushan–rishathaim king of Mesopotamia: and the children of Israel served Chushan–rishathaim eight years.
verses.verse_html:
8Therefore the anger of the Lord was hot against Israel, and he sold them into the hand of Chushan–rishathaim king of Mesopotamia: and the children of Israel served Chushan–rishathaim eight years. ▼
▼ Mesopotamia: Heb. Aram–naharaim

verses.text_plain: And when the children of Israel cried unto the Lord, the Lord raised up a deliverer to the children of Israel, who delivered them, even Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb’s younger brother.
verses.verse_html:
9And when the children of Israel cried unto the Lord, the Lord raised up a deliverer to the children of Israel, who delivered them, even Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb’s younger brother. ▼
▼ deliverer: Heb. saviour

verses.text_plain: And the Spirit of the Lord came upon him, and he judged Israel, and went out to war: and the Lord delivered Chushan–rishathaim king of Mesopotamia into his hand; and his hand prevailed against Chushan–rishathaim.
verses.verse_html:
10And the Spirit of the Lord came upon him, and he judged Israel, and went out to war: and the Lord delivered Chushan–rishathaim king of Mesopotamia into his hand; and his hand prevailed against Chushan–rishathaim. ▼
▼ came: Heb. was
 , ▼
▼ Mesopotamia: Heb. Aram

tokens.text: came upon him, and he judged

verses.text_plain: And the land had rest forty years. And Othniel the son of Kenaz died.
verses.verse_html: 11And the land had rest forty years. And Othniel the son of Kenaz died.

verses.text_plain: And the children of Israel did evil again in the sight of the Lord: and the Lord strengthened Eglon the king of Moab against Israel, because they had done evil in the sight of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 12And the children of Israel did evil again in the sight of the Lord: and the Lord strengthened Eglon the king of Moab against Israel, because they had done evil in the sight of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And he gathered unto him the children of Ammon and Amalek, and went and smote Israel, and possessed the city of palm trees.
verses.verse_html: 13And he gathered unto him the children of Ammon and Amalek, and went and smote Israel, and possessed the city of palm trees.

verses.text_plain: So the children of Israel served Eglon the king of Moab eighteen years.
verses.verse_html: 14So the children of Israel served Eglon the king of Moab eighteen years.

verses.text_plain: But when the children of Israel cried unto the Lord, the Lord raised them up a deliverer, Ehud the son of Gera, a Benjamite, a man lefthanded: and by him the children of Israel sent a present unto Eglon the king of Moab.
verses.verse_html:
15But when the children of Israel cried unto the Lord, the Lord raised them up a deliverer, Ehud the son of Gera, a Benjamite, a man lefthanded: and by him the children of Israel sent a present unto Eglon the king of Moab. ▼
▼ a Benjamite: or, the son of Jemini
 , ▼
▼ lefthanded: Heb. shut of his right hand

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a Benjamite: or, the son of Jemini
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a Benjamite: or, the son of Jemini

footnotes.body_text: ▼ lefthanded: Heb. shut of his right hand
footnotes.body_html: ▼ lefthanded: Heb. shut of his right hand

verses.text_plain: But Ehud made him a dagger which had two edges, of a cubit length; and he did gird it under his raiment upon his right thigh.
verses.verse_html: 16But Ehud made him a dagger which had two edges, of a cubit length; and he did gird it under his raiment upon his right thigh.

verses.text_plain: And he brought the present unto Eglon king of Moab: and Eglon was a very fat man.
verses.verse_html: 17And he brought the present unto Eglon king of Moab: and Eglon was a very fat man.

verses.text_plain: And when he had made an end to offer the present, he sent away the people that bare the present.
verses.verse_html: 18And when he had made an end to offer the present, he sent away the people that bare the present.

tokens.text: And when he had made an end

verses.text_plain: But he himself turned again from the quarries that were by Gilgal, and said, I have a secret errand unto thee, O king: who said, Keep silence. And all that stood by him went out from him.
verses.verse_html:
19But he himself turned again from the quarries that were by Gilgal, and said, I have a secret errand unto thee, O king: who said, Keep silence. And all that stood by him went out from him. ▼
▼ quarries: or, graven images

footnotes.body_html: ▼ quarries: or, graven images

verses.text_plain: And Ehud came unto him; and he was sitting in a summer parlour, which he had for himself alone. And Ehud said, I have a message from God unto thee. And he arose out of his seat.
verses.verse_html:
20And Ehud came unto him; and he was sitting in a summer parlour, which he had for himself alone. And Ehud said, I have a message from God unto thee. And he arose out of his seat. ▼
▼ a summer…: Heb. a parlour of cooling

tokens.text: unto him; and he was sitting
which he had for himself alone. And Ehud

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a summer…: Heb. a parlour of cooling
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a summer…: Heb. a parlour of cooling

verses.text_plain: And Ehud put forth his left hand, and took the dagger from his right thigh, and thrust it into his belly:
verses.verse_html: 21And Ehud put forth his left hand, and took the dagger from his right thigh, and thrust it into his belly:

verses.text_plain: And the haft also went in after the blade; and the fat closed upon the blade, so that he could not draw the dagger out of his belly; and the dirt came out.
verses.verse_html:
22And the haft also went in after the blade; and the fat closed upon the blade, so that he could not draw the dagger out of his belly; and the dirt came out. ▼
▼ the dirt…: or, it came out at the buttocks

tokens.text: so that he could not draw

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the dirt…: or, it came out at the buttocks
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the dirt…: or, it came out at the buttocks

verses.text_plain: Then Ehud went forth through the porch, and shut the doors of the parlour upon him, and locked them.
verses.verse_html: 23Then Ehud went forth through the porch, and shut the doors of the parlour upon him, and locked them.

verses.text_plain: When he was gone out, his servants came; and when they saw that, behold, the doors of the parlour were locked, they said, Surely he covereth his feet in his summer chamber.
verses.verse_html:
24When he was gone out, his servants came; and when they saw that, behold, the doors of the parlour were locked, they said, Surely he covereth his feet in his summer chamber. ▼
▼ covereth…: or, doeth his easement

footnotes.body_html: ▼ covereth…: or, doeth his easement

verses.text_plain: And they tarried till they were ashamed: and, behold, he opened not the doors of the parlour; therefore they took a key, and opened them: and, behold, their lord was fallen down dead on the earth.
verses.verse_html: 25And they tarried till they were ashamed: and, behold, he opened not the doors of the parlour; therefore they took a key, and opened them: and, behold, their lord was fallen down dead on the earth.

verses.text_plain: And Ehud escaped while they tarried, and passed beyond the quarries, and escaped unto Seirath.
verses.verse_html: 26And Ehud escaped while they tarried, and passed beyond the quarries, and escaped unto Seirath.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, when he was come, that he blew a trumpet in the mountain of Ephraim, and the children of Israel went down with him from the mount, and he before them.
verses.verse_html: 27And it came to pass, when he was come, that he blew a trumpet in the mountain of Ephraim, and the children of Israel went down with him from the mount, and he before them.

tokens.text: And it came to pass, when he was come

verses.text_plain: And he said unto them, Follow after me: for the Lord hath delivered your enemies the Moabites into your hand. And they went down after him, and took the fords of Jordan toward Moab, and suffered not a man to pass over.
verses.verse_html: 28And he said unto them, Follow after me: for the Lord hath delivered your enemies the Moabites into your hand. And they went down after him, and took the fords of Jordan toward Moab, and suffered not a man to pass over.

verses.text_plain: And they slew of Moab at that time about ten thousand men, all lusty, and all men of valour; and there escaped not a man.
verses.verse_html:
29And they slew of Moab at that time about ten thousand men, all lusty, and all men of valour; and there escaped not a man. ▼
▼ lusty: Heb. fat

verses.text_plain: So Moab was subdued that day under the hand of Israel. And the land had rest fourscore years.
verses.verse_html: 30So Moab was subdued that day under the hand of Israel. And the land had rest fourscore years.

verses.text_plain: And after him was Shamgar the son of Anath, which slew of the Philistines six hundred men with an ox goad: and he also delivered Israel.
verses.verse_html: 31And after him was Shamgar the son of Anath, which slew of the Philistines six hundred men with an ox goad: and he also delivered Israel.
